\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mandri, Art is objective. There are objective measures. If you get 100 people in a room, and 90 will say that this is the best work in the house.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I disagree.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Do you? I should say, if you do, then you\u8217\'92ve been corrupted by degenerate culture, dear Vigram.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, I don\u8217\'92t think so. I simply don\u8217\'92t see how adding subjective measures together creates an objective measure. These are fundamentally different things.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 An object stands on its own. It is independent of the artist. It\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s quality, its success, depends on how well the artist pulled from the Allwhite.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Salavan, you can\u8217\'92t be serious. There is only subjective taste! Tastes can overlap, sure, but where they do, it\u8217\'92s no guarantee of quality. You say, everyone agrees that this painting, }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 this}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  painting here, is a great work. Well, I think there\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s very little good in that painting. In my eye, Boogaloo was chasing a trend. I don\u8217\'92t like it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Neither do I\u8221\'94, said Mandri}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Hah! That makes two against one! A quorum has been reached; an objective measure! Objectively, then, that painting is a failure.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Vigram. I wont have this . Consider the issue deeply. There is a reason, a fundamental reason, why this painting is known throughout the world, and that one is not.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Of course there\u8217\'92s a reason. That\u8217\'92s because it was stolen at least five times! That\u8217\'92s it! Two hundred years ago, that painting was hardly listed amongst Cavalan\u8217\'92s works.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93But *why* was it stolen? There is something about the work that--"}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "It was stolen because it was easy to steal!"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "This was }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 not}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  easy to steal."\line }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Of course it was, now that it has value. I mean, originally, back when--}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "This is all beside the point, Vigram. I'm not saying that there is no such thing as personal preference. Personal preference is simply one dimension which determines a work's quality. Preference, subjectivity, it should not drown out all the other factors surrounding a work. When all factors are accounted for, an objective measure can be made.}
